META ANALYSIS â€” Analysis Page

The META ANALYSIS panel is not a real-time widget.
It is a delayed, log-based analysis tool designed to provide a macro-level view of radio activity.

It is based on the application log (radio_spot_watcher.log) and answers a simple question:

What actually happened over time, beyond the real-time spot flow?

What META ANALYSIS does

Parses the application log

Extracts valid DX spots

Cleans duplicates and noise

Aggregates data over a defined time range

Produces structured summary files used by the UI

How it works

META ANALYSIS runs in manual daily mode:

No automatic cron execution

One analysis run per 24 hours

Triggered manually via the RUN button

This design choice is intentional:
it favors reliable, calm analysis over continuous recalculation.

What it is not

It does not predict propagation

It does not replace real-time monitoring

It does not provide automatic recommendations

META ANALYSIS documents recent past activity to support better understanding and decision-making.



